examples.en: They asked us, nay, begged us.
Nay, I do not wish to go.
I have weighty, nay, unanswerable reasons to think so.
Each of us is peculiar, nay, in a sense unique.
Mr. Herbert demanded the yeas and nays.
I was angrynay, furiousat the way they were treating that poor dog.
A Bill has passed the H.R. repealing the duty on salt with only 5 nays.
When the votes were tallied, it was 241 yeas and 54 nays.
